{"source_key":"sha256-300730d11a7046aaae6c4eb40315fa44","record_index":257,"record_hash":"sha256:6788bdfde1fbf4702d520b5ef33da0d13311069676723a928370c0bb757fe8b0","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:04:58.088Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Top Issues**\\n\\n1. **The doc still has old blockers mixed with resolved decisions.**  \\n   `Current Decisions`, `Open Questions`, `Pre-Build Decisions`, and `Remaining Answers Needed` disagree with each other. A builder will waste time re-litigating snapshots, live updates, forks, metadata refs, cache invalidation, UI wireframe, and publication boundary.\\n\\n2. **MVP entry point is muddy.**  \\n   Early text says “GitButler adds a link to the PR,” but the actual MVP is now on-demand URL replacement. Pick URL replacement as v1; move PR comments/descriptions/check-runs to later.\\n\\n3. **Publication/privacy language is still too vague for public v1.**  \\n   Since v1 is public repos + public metadata + no extra redaction, say plainly: on-demand URL replacement may generate a public snapshot only from publicly fetchable metadata. Private sharing/publication review is out of scope.\\n\\n4. **Change lookup still leaks into the MVP text.**  \\n   The doc says change lookup is not relevant, but later says “PR/branch/change” and “pull request, branch, review, or change target.” Remove change from all MVP flows.\\n\\n5. **Metadata fetch policy needs one clean sentence.**  \\n   The v1 decision is: fetch only `refs/meta/main` from the public GitHub repo resolved from the PR URL. Mentions of configured metadata remotes should move to “Later.”\\n\\n6. **Snapshot URL semantics are underspecified.**  \\n   You decided snapshot identity, but not whether the public PR-style URL shows “latest generated snapshot” or redirects to an immutable snapshot URL. Builders need this before wiring routes/cache.\\n\\n**Suggested Doc Changes**\\n\\nAdd a short **MVP Contract** near the top:\\n\\n```text\\nInput: https://agent-trail.gitbutler.com/<owner>/<repo>/pull/<number>\\nScope: public GitHub repos only, no forks\\nMetadata: fetch refs/meta/main from the public repo\\nLookup: review target gitbutler-review:<number> + PR head branch\\nRanking: review matches above branch-only matches\\nOutput: generated snapshot page with overview + session/turn drill-down\\n```\\n\\nRewrite **Non-Goals** to explicitly include:\\n\\n- private repos\\n- fork PRs\\n- GitHub OAuth\\n- configurable metadata remotes\\n- check-run/GitHub app integration\\n- change-target lookup\\n- user session exclusion/hiding\\n- generated summaries as required MVP behavior\\n\\nCollapse **Open Questions**, **Pre-Build Decisions**, and **Remaining Answers Needed** into two sections:\\n\\n- **Resolved For MVP**\\n- **Deferred**\\n\\nThat will make the doc much more usable for agentic development.\\n\\n**Must-Ask Questions**\\n\\nOnly one, and it matters before building:\\n\\nShould the URL-replacement route render the latest generated snapshot in place, or redirect to an immutable snapshot URL once generation succeeds?\\n\\nMy pick: **stable PR URL renders/latest-generates; immutable snapshot id stays internal for now.** Simpler UX, less routing ceremony.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:04:58.088Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}